transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes sir, I'm calling to see if my order has been shipped out yet.

Speaker 1: What's your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Keith Hawkins, H-A-W-K-I-N-S.

Speaker 1: Let me see what's going on here, Mr. Hawkins.

Speaker 2: Oh yeah, we spoke yesterday.

Speaker 1: Yes sir, your order has been shipped out, you're good to go Mr. Hawkins.

Speaker 2: Yeah, as soon as you're going to see it arrive in the next few days, I have a tracking number here for you if you want it.

Speaker 1: You can send it over.

Speaker 2: Did y'all send me an email?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'll send it to you now. I have it here, so I'll have your email.

Speaker 2: I'll re-send it for you, it might have got corrupted or something, but I'll re-send it for you right now while I have you on the phone.

Speaker 1: When do you think that package is going to arrive because I paid for it to be here quicker?

Speaker 2: It should be there, it's saying Monday.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I told them on the phone it'll probably be here tomorrow, but Monday.

Speaker 2: Okay, alright, thank you.

Speaker 1: No problem, thank you.
